: false, "domain": "media.patriots.win", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASYytrmqK.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://media.patriots.win/post/1AyRo0AzjtuY.jpeg", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/NdUZIWB3RxxIStnI.jpeg", "width": 768, "content-type": "jpeg", "height": 292}], "blurhash": "U2Rp8-00_2004n8_4mIA?bxuxuRjxvkD%g~q", "full_resolution": [447, 1177]}, "title": "One Time While Teaching CPR CHUCK NORRIS Brought the Dummy to LIFE ! ", "last_comment_created": 1774036265296, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 1, "score_up": 34, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASYysj7H6", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 135, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8501018, "raw_content": "Supply and Demand drive the price of nearly everything.  The population of the US is over 340 million people, but without the people that have illegally entered our country and their kids, the population of the US would be ~260 million today.   The illegal aliends are _ times more likely to be on some sort of welfare system.  That is taking away from American citizens.\n\nRemoving cheap labor would hurt big businesses, which is also why so many politicians are taking lobby $$$ to support illegal immigration.  \n\nBut we also have to look at our young people.  Why can't they afford a house?  Because there is too much demand.  If you removed nearly 25% of the US population, most on welfare, then the demand on houses and property would drop and young people could easily afford a home.   \n\nLets summarize where the illegal immigrants are helping and hurting America:\n\nHelp the rich, help the politicians.  ($$$ and power)\n\nHurt everyone else.  (traffic, education (~$20k/yr for public education per student), housing, medical, welfare, anything impacted by supply/demand (from food to gas to new cars)) \n\nI don't blame them from wanting a better life in American, but we are sacrificing our citizens, especially the young people to support them.  \n", "author": "Beer-_-Belly", "created": 1774006905099, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Gulleyfoyleismyname", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Republican politicians need to make a point of supply/demand and how illegals have driven up rent and the cost of homes for young people.", "last_comment_created": 1774022161409, "content": "<p>Supply and Demand drive the price of nearly everything.  The population of the US is over 340 million people, but without the people that have illegally entered our country and their kids, the population of the US would be ~260 million today.   The illegal aliends are _ times more likely to be on some sort of welfare system.  That is taking away from American citizens.</p>\n<p>Removing cheap labor would hurt big businesses, which is also why so many politicians are taking lobby $$$ to support illegal immigration.</p>\n<p>But we also have to look at our young people.  Why can't they afford a house?  Because there is too much demand.  If you removed nearly 25% of the US population, most on welfare, then the demand on houses and property would drop and young people could easily afford a home.</p>\n<p>Lets summarize where the illegal immigrants are helping and hurting America:</p>\n<p>Help the rich, help the politicians.  ($$$ and power)</p>\n<p>Hurt everyone else.  (traffic, education (~$20k/yr for public education per student), housing, medical, welfare, anything impacted by supply/demand (from food to gas to new cars))</p>\n<p>I don't blame them from wanting a better life in American, but we are sacrificing our citizens, especially the young people to support them.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 9, "score_up": 135, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2034755543894749490", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASYyraikm", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 1441, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "censored", "id": 8500014, "raw_content": "", "author": "DebunkTheLeft", "created": 1773959475639, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "behemoth887", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASYyraikm.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/ksorbs/status/2034755543894749490", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "So Nick Shirley discovered billions of dollars of fraud in Minnesota at the hands of the Somali community. And Somalia is currently experiencing a massive boom in new buildings being built.", "last_comment_created": 1774018515265, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 85, "score_up": 1441, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, 